      "content": "The strongest philosophical argument is that government regulation inherently creates a \"chilling effect,\" where the fear of state punishment silences dissent before it even occurs, fundamentally undermining the First Amendment's core purpose.\nFurthermore, the concept of \"prior restraint\" is so dangerous that any regulatory framework, no matter how well-intentioned, inevitably grants the state unchecked power to decide what speech is permissible.\nUltimately, the only true safeguard for free speech is a complete absence of government interference, as even the appearance of regulation invites corruption and censorship.",
